  <name>Power Scheduler</name>
  <summary>Schedule Linux power actions without keeping the app open</summary>
  <description>
    <p>
      Power Scheduler lets you delay lock, log out, suspend, hibernate or
      power off your Linux system. Actions are scheduled through systemd
      transient timers so they survive even when you close the application.
    </p>
  </description>
